        content: 'Review the NCEES FS Exam Specifications document, which lists all reference materials provided during the exam and the percentage of questions allocated to each domain. The NSPS website (nsps.us.com) publishes the Model Standards for Professional Surveying Practice. Your state board of licensure publishes the state-specific minimum standards that may be tested on the state-specific portion of the PS exam (though not the FS exam). Practice with the NCEES Practice Exam, which uses the same interface as the actual CBT exam and includes the same reference materials. During your practice sessions, time yourself on standards-based questions to develop the speed needed for exam day. Key resources to review include the ALTA/NSPS standards document, the FEMA Elevation Certificate form and instructions, the FGCS leveling specifications, and the FGDC Geospatial Positioning Accuracy Standards Part 3 (NSSDA).',
